Introduction

This code of conduct outlines the expected behavior for all contributors and users of the [Your Simple Interest Calculator Project Name] project. We are dedicated to fostering a welcoming and inclusive community where everyone feels safe and respected.

Values

We value:

Respect: Treat all individuals with courtesy and respect, regardless of their background, experience, or beliefs.
Openness: Encourage open communication and collaboration.
Inclusiveness: Welcome and value contributions from everyone, regardless of their identity or experience.
Constructive criticism: Provide feedback in a constructive and helpful manner.
Professionalism: Maintain a professional and respectful tone in all interactions.
Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are not tolerated in our community:

Discrimination: Harassment, discrimination, or offensive language based on any protected attribute, such as race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, religion, age, disability, or socio-economic status.
Personal attacks: Insulting, threatening, or demeaning language directed at others.
Unwanted attention: Making unwelcome advances or requests for attention.
Doxing or sharing private information: Sharing personal information about others without their consent.
Spam or off-topic communication: Sending irrelevant or promotional messages.
Disruptive behavior: Intentionally disrupting discussions or projects.
Violating the terms of this code of conduct.
Reporting Unacceptable Behavior

If you experience or witness any unacceptable behavior, please report it immediately to [Insert reporting contact information, e.g., email address, issue tracker]. We will investigate all reports promptly and take appropriate action.

Consequences of Unacceptable Behavior

Violations of this code of conduct may result in a range of consequences, including:

Warnings or admonitions.
Temporary or permanent suspension from the project.
Removal of contributions.
Legal action.
Commitment

We are committed to creating and maintaining a positive and productive community. We encourage everyone to contribute to this goal by following this code of conduct and treating each other with respect.

Thank you for your cooperation!
